Okay food... terrible service. During this COVID-19 pandemic you’d think the people would be nice and considerate... FIRST THINGS FIRST, I ordered for pick-up. Because of the covid-19 I didn’t feel comfortable checking my food before I left the restaurant to check if it was right or not... (maybe that was my mistake but still, as a paying customer you expect your order to be correct) So I got home. Over the phone, I ordered 2 sopes, 2 quesadillas & 1 huarache. Problem #1: I ended up with 1 sope instead of 2... problem #2: half the tortilla for my huarache was uncooked. (I am Mexican. My mom makes her tortillas so I KNOW when a tortilla is fully cooked.) & my huarache came WITHOUT the meat I ordered (which they charge you extra for). SECONDLY, when I finished eating the food, unsatisfied, I called the restaurant to let them know my concerns and the errors in my order. Halfway through talking & explaining what was wrong after the lady on the phone asked the second time, she HUNG UP ON ME. I called again right after, even more upset, and it beeped as if the number was disconnected. The food was sub-par. It was ok. But being charged for stuff I didn’t get & then getting hung up on was annoying. This was my third time eating from this place (all other times the food was eh also) & needless to say, not ordering from this place again. There are 2 other Mexican spots near this place that I’d rather take my $$ to.
